Package: zipd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 Zip is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Zip uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Zip Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the daemon, zipd, and the CLI tool
 zip-cli to interact with the daemon.

Package: zip-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 Zip is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Zip uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Zip Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides Zip-Qt, a GUI for Zip based on Qt.

Package: zip-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 Zip is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Zip uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Zip Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides zip-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a zip daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
